"{\"uid\": \"businessinsider.com-french-air-traffic-controllers-olympics-allowed-turn-up-hours-late-2024-5\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Every time Pete publishes a story, you will get an alert straight to your inbox!\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 80, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Enter your email    By clicking \\\"Sign up\\\", you agree to receive emails from Business Insider.\", \"from\": 82, \"to\": 175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 158, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Business_Insider\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Business Insider\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Business_Insider\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Business_Insider\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, you accept Insider'sTerms of ServiceandPrivacy Policy.\", \"from\": 176, \"to\": 243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Frenchair traffic controllershave been given the legal right to turn up three hours late for work, and leave three hours early,Les Echosreported.\", \"from\": 245, \"to\": 390, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's because the National Union for Air Traffic Controllers (SNCTA) reached an agreement that includes ending a practice called \\\"clearances\\\" - where staff could leave work during quiet periods, according to the French newspaper.\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 605, \"end\": 611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9852487541061342, \"rank\": 0.01263964694971422, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because ending \\\"clearances\\\" led to more working hours, the controllers are now authorized to arrive three hours late or leave three hours early, when traffic permits.\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 790, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It means Frenchair traffic controllershave a mandatory minimum time on the clock of five hours, according to Les Echos.\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 911, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The details of the agreement were kept quiet after the SNCTA reached a deal with the government to avoid a strike on April 25.\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With theOlympicstaking place in France this year, politicians were eager to avoid any potential disruption at airports.\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1072, \"end\": 1078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.4750436647855515, \"rank\": 0.7098173752964267, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a big win for the SNCTA and highlights the strength of labor unions in France.\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1237, \"end\": 1243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.4750436647855515, \"rank\": 0.7098173752964267, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Air traffic controllers also won several other benefits as part of the deal, according to Les Echos.\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1346, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That includes an additional 18 days off work, and retirement at age 59.\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Plus, Les Echos reported their salaries are set to go up by an average of 1,500 euros a month, spread over four years.\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1426, \"end\": 1435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Echos_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9960860726799544, \"rank\": 0.003929177783167692, \"text\": \"Les Echos\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Echos_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Echos_(France)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's around an extra $19,400 a year.\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1577, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Agence France-Press reported in 2022 that the averageFrench air traffic controller earned $59,820 a year- putting the recent pay increase at around a third.\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1735, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1579, \"end\": 1598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agence France-Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The report added that the deal will be entirely financed by airlines.\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a further three days of strikes were planned for this month, a person familiar with the matter told Les Echos that forAir France, the cost of further strike action could have outweighed the compensation given to the air traffic controllers.\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1932, \"end\": 1938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.4750436647855515, \"rank\": 0.7098173752964267, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jump to\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2059, \"entities\": []}]}"